gov.va.med.lom.foundation.util

Class ListBasedComparator

  • java.lang.Object
    • gov.va.med.lom.foundation.util.ListBasedComparator
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.util.Comparator

    public class ListBasedComparator
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.util.Comparator
    Comparator class useful for determining order based on objects' position in a list. When comparing 2 object, this comparator will return a value based on where the object appears in the list. So, if a list contains the following: ('foo', 'bar'), 'foo' is said to be 'less than' bar when performing a compare (-1). If an item is not found in the list, it will return 'greater than' (+1) an item found in the list, or 'equals' to another object not in the list (0).
